1
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:13,040
Good morning. First of all, I bring you greetings from our sister church, Warm Springs Baptist Church of Las Vegas, Nevada,

2
00:00:13,460 --> 00:00:18,380
where we as a staff had spent the past few days as part of our annual conference.

3
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:24,400
And the theme of the conference was, This Man Welcomes Sinners, Do We?

4
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:30,520
And so to be in Las Vegas, we felt like it was an appropriate place for the churches to gather.

5
00:00:30,520 --> 00:00:34,530
and I had the privilege of sharing with my staff

6
00:00:34,530 --> 00:00:36,170
and spending time on the strip with them

7
00:00:36,170 --> 00:00:37,610
eating well for very cheap

8
00:00:37,610 --> 00:00:40,450
and yet really thinking through

9
00:00:40,450 --> 00:00:42,890
do we really care for all these lost people

10
00:00:42,890 --> 00:00:46,630
that seem to concentrate so much there in that city

11
00:00:46,630 --> 00:00:48,850
but they're everywhere aren't they

12
00:00:48,850 --> 00:00:51,290
and it is our job and our duty

13
00:00:51,290 --> 00:00:53,590
and our responsibility and our privilege

14
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:55,790
to bring the love of Jesus Christ to them

15
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:57,610
in any way that we can

16
00:00:57,610 --> 00:01:00,510
and so we were really challenged in different ways

17
00:01:00,510 --> 00:01:06,010
and had an opportunity to hear Lee Strobel, the man who wrote The Case for Christ and The Case for Faith,

18
00:01:06,090 --> 00:01:10,270
as he spoke to us and encouraged us, and we just had a blast.

19
00:01:10,970 --> 00:01:14,850
And then while we were there, of course, the angels were still kind of up and down,

20
00:01:14,910 --> 00:01:17,890
and the bookies were running around, and it was really quite a scene.

21
00:01:18,730 --> 00:01:21,850
And I'll tell you, after last night, my heart can't take that anymore.

22
00:01:24,580 --> 00:01:29,820
Now, who would have thought, beginning of this year, we'd be right here moving our pastor's class up an hour,

23
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:33,820
that we might see that and also learn about our church.

24
00:01:34,180 --> 00:01:35,980
So, a lot of fun things.

25
00:01:36,780 --> 00:01:39,660
I finally do want to say that if you've been blessed by Kit's testimony

26
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:42,940
and want to be part of her ministry and prayer and support,

27
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,900
she's got an email sign up at the back.

28
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:48,160
You can let her know your email and she'll keep in touch with you,

29
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,400
as she will this church.

30
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:53,160
We are one of her friendly churches that we love her on the West Coast.

31
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:56,640
And we want to keep track of your ministry and be a part of that.

32
00:01:56,640 --> 00:02:00,040
And we may come see you, and you may come pick us up at the airport.

33
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:02,900
And that would be very fun as we minister in Thailand.

34
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,200
So get your chopsticks out.

35
00:02:04,260 --> 00:02:06,520
You never know what the Lord may do.

36
00:02:07,490 --> 00:02:09,830
Well, there's a lot happening in our world, isn't there?

37
00:02:09,890 --> 00:02:14,650
I mean, in just a few days' time, the newspapers can send you all over the place.

38
00:02:14,650 --> 00:02:17,890
I mean, now North Korea has the bomb.

39
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:25,320
The tentacles of terrorism have gripped many parts of our world and continue to do so.

40
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:30,980
A shooter had the Washington area living in abject fear on a daily basis.

41
00:02:32,180 --> 00:02:36,620
Stocks have been down, down, down, and then up, up, up.

42
00:02:36,660 --> 00:02:39,420
And the question is, where is it going next?

43
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:43,320
Companies are downsizing in order to survive.

44
00:02:44,780 --> 00:02:46,980
It hits my family particularly closely.

45
00:02:46,980 --> 00:02:53,740
My father worked for United Airlines for over 30 years, a stable, major carrier out there.

46
00:02:53,740 --> 00:03:00,240
and for them to threaten downsizing reorganization or chapters 7, 11, or 13

47
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:03,840
is just beyond what we can imagine.

48
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:08,720
Stability just suddenly taken out impacts our life.

49
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:11,800
It's hard to even imagine those kinds of changes.

50
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:16,060
But that's our world, an uncertain world, most certainly.

51
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:22,000
But the uncertainties in our world that are certain that there's going to be uncertainties

52
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:28,480
and continue to be so, those come from the foibles and the failure of human beings,

53
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:31,570
but not from the hand of God.

54
00:03:32,730 --> 00:03:37,160
Those are decisions by humans, not from God.

55
00:03:38,820 --> 00:03:41,840
And in the midst of all that, how do we keep our head?

56
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:46,140
How do we stay stable in the midst of all those changes?

57
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:52,980
How do you live under God's blessing instead of in the vicissitudes of the decisions made by human beings?

58
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:59,730
How do we stay out of the trap of riding that roller coaster with the world?

59
00:03:59,730 --> 00:04:04,810
How do we stay close to the Lord under His blessing in uncertain times?

60
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:09,820
Well, in this second message, as we talk about stewardship,

61
00:04:10,940 --> 00:04:13,460
I think we have some answers to share this morning.

62
00:04:14,950 --> 00:04:19,850
And I just want to say, if you want blessing in your life, listen to this message.

63
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:27,370
But more importantly, do this message.

64
00:04:28,940 --> 00:04:30,480
It's one thing to hear it.

65
00:04:30,740 --> 00:04:32,980
It's another thing to do it.

66
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,500
And the Scriptures teach that.

67
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:39,560
Be doers of the Word, says James 1, verse 22.

68
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:46,040
Be doers of the Word and not merely hearers who deceive themselves.

69
00:04:47,590 --> 00:04:52,390
Will we as Fullerton first be doers of God's Word?

70
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:58,540
I'd like for us to consider a man who struggled with doing God's Word.

71
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,080
It comes out of Mark chapter 10.

72
00:05:02,590 --> 00:05:03,930
And I will read this.

73
00:05:04,050 --> 00:05:05,650
Follow along in your Bibles around the screen.

74
00:05:06,510 --> 00:05:10,070
In the New Living Translation, Mark 10 verse 17.

75
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:19,380
As he was starting out on a trip, a man came running up to Jesus, knelt down, and asked,

76
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:23,360
Good teacher, what should I do to get eternal life?

77
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:26,100
Why do you call me good?

78
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:27,480
Jesus asked.

79
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,880
Only God is truly good.

80
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:33,340
But as for your question, you know the commandments.

81
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:41,820
Do not murder, do not commit adultery, do not steal, do not testify falsely, do not cheat.

82
00:05:42,420 --> 00:05:44,000
Honor your father and mother.

83
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:49,900
Teacher, the man replied, I've obeyed all these commandments since I was a child.

84
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:55,280
Jesus felt genuine love for this man and looked at him.

85
00:05:56,470 --> 00:05:58,490
You lack only one thing, he told him.

86
00:05:59,170 --> 00:06:05,710
Go and sell all you have and give the money to the poor and you will have treasure in heaven.

87
00:06:06,940 --> 00:06:08,620
Then come, follow me.

88
00:06:10,180 --> 00:06:15,820
At this the man's face fell and he went sadly away because he had many possessions.

89
00:06:19,090 --> 00:06:22,770
From the other recordings of this event, from the other gospel writers,

90
00:06:22,770 --> 00:06:27,290
we know that this man who came to Jesus was young.

91
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:30,140
We know he was a religious leader.

92
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:32,550
We know he was rich.

93
00:06:33,940 --> 00:06:39,460
And in various editorial titles in Scripture, he's referred to as the rich young ruler.

94
00:06:41,290 --> 00:06:42,390
So let's talk about that.

95
00:06:42,490 --> 00:06:43,810
First of all, he was rich.

96
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:45,560
He had money.

97
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,920
And with money comes options.

98
00:06:50,460 --> 00:06:52,660
Options to do what you'd please.

99
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:57,580
With wealth, you can pretty much do whatever you want.

100
00:06:58,990 --> 00:07:00,370
And that's not a bad thing, is it?

101
00:07:00,970 --> 00:07:03,770
You can grow, you can further yourself, you can see the world.

102
00:07:03,770 --> 00:07:06,110
You can do many things with wealth.

103
00:07:06,630 --> 00:07:08,030
Wealth can be a good thing.

104
00:07:09,290 --> 00:07:13,270
It can give you phenomenal opportunities that others do not have.

105
00:07:14,890 --> 00:07:20,330
It can give you opportunities to bless others in ways that others cannot do.

106
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:22,530
Wealth can be a wonderful thing.

107
00:07:24,350 --> 00:07:26,650
The man was a religious leader, a ruler.

108
00:07:28,180 --> 00:07:30,700
In other words, this man had influence.

109
00:07:32,110 --> 00:07:32,930
He was a leader.

110
00:07:32,930 --> 00:07:36,910
He could make things happen within those that he led.

111
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:42,880
And I think from the text, if you read it carefully, I think he was a nice guy.

112
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:44,560
I really do.

113
00:07:45,770 --> 00:07:48,170
He was respectful as he approached Jesus.

114
00:07:49,370 --> 00:07:51,650
He knelt before him, a sign of submission.

115
00:07:52,990 --> 00:07:55,070
And Jesus had great compassion for him.

116
00:07:55,630 --> 00:08:00,870
And just putting those two things together, I seem to sense that he was probably a nice guy.

117
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:05,090
A nice, rich leader who was young.

118
00:08:06,150 --> 00:08:08,690
Matthew 19.20 says that he was a young man.

119
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:12,660
And a young man or woman, they have time on their side.

120
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,420
This man had a lot of opportunities.

121
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:20,900
He had money, he had some power, perhaps a charismatic personality.

122
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,140
He had time.

123
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:26,260
He had, in the world's eyes, a lot of things in his favor.

124
00:08:28,140 --> 00:08:29,260
I think I would have liked him.

125
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:33,530
I probably would have invited him to church and enjoyed him.

126
00:08:33,530 --> 00:08:36,390
I think we might even nominate him to the trustee board.

127
00:08:36,470 --> 00:08:37,650
He's a good, rich, young ruler.

128
00:08:37,770 --> 00:08:39,670
This is the kind of guy we want on our team.

129
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:44,610
And he asks a very important question.

130
00:08:45,270 --> 00:08:48,070
He asks the all-important question.

131
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:55,210
He asked the $64,000 question, what should I do to obtain eternal life?

132
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:02,660
And after demonstrating that he knew the Scriptures, had done all that's required by the law,

133
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:05,660
Jesus said that he lacked one thing.

134
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:08,310
And that's all it takes, isn't it?

135
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:10,310
One thing.

136
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:13,020
And that's my first point this morning.

137
00:09:14,050 --> 00:09:16,970
One thing can make the difference.

138
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,560
One thing.

139
00:09:20,140 --> 00:09:26,940
It's amazing how one small thing can cause a disaster or bring about a triumph.

140
00:09:28,690 --> 00:09:32,900
The space shuttle Challenger, one crack in the O-rings,

141
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:38,220
brought down the most sophisticated piece of machinery that human beings had ever developed,

142
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:42,280
not to mention losing the lives of the seven astronauts aboard.

143
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:45,240
One crack, one thing brought it down.

144
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:48,800
One crack of a bat can change history.

145
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:50,520
Turn a game.

146
00:09:52,050 --> 00:09:53,010
Change the World Series.

147
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:54,790
One small thing.

148
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:56,520
Amen.

149
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:57,180
Amen.

150
00:09:57,300 --> 00:09:58,220
That's a good place for an amen.

151
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:02,720
May there be more cracks of bats this afternoon in our favor.

152
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:06,970
It's amazing the power of one small thing, isn't it?

153
00:10:06,970 --> 00:10:09,530
One moment in time can change history.

154
00:10:09,950 --> 00:10:13,930
One moment in your time can change your history.

155
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:20,880
One decision to follow Jesus Christ can change your life forever,

156
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:25,140
both here and for literally ever and ever.

157
00:10:27,650 --> 00:10:32,910
And one stubborn refusal to acknowledge Jesus as director of heaven and earth

158
00:10:32,910 --> 00:10:36,550
can produce the most miserable eternity imaginable.

159
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:40,330
One small thing can change your life.

160
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:44,520
It's amazing the power of one thing.

161
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:48,170
It only takes one thing to keep you out of heaven.

162
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:55,270
For the young man, the rich young ruler, it was one thing.

163
00:10:56,820 --> 00:10:57,300
One thing.

164
00:10:58,140 --> 00:11:00,560
He was in love with his possessions.

165
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:03,360
He was in love with his position.

166
00:11:03,860 --> 00:11:05,880
He was in love with his pride.

167
00:11:08,370 --> 00:11:11,170
And he walked away from Jesus downcast.

168
00:11:11,410 --> 00:11:16,850
He wanted eternal life, but he wanted the tangible goodies even more.

169
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:20,700
It's been said this.

170
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:24,640
He wasn't willing to let go of the gold.

171
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:27,040
He wasn't willing.

172
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:32,380
There's a deeper principle at work here.

173
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:35,100
And I want us to get to this truth.

174
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:37,960
To get, you have to give.

175
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:41,430
To get, you have to give.

176
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:43,780
It's a biblical idea.

177
00:11:44,260 --> 00:11:47,220
Matthew 10, verse 39, Jesus says,

178
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:51,230
If you cling to your life, you will lose it.

179
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:55,180
But if you give it up for me, you will find it.

180
00:11:55,180 --> 00:12:09,620
Mark 10 31 but many who are first will be last and the last first one simple

181
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:18,140
thing can make all the difference now what would have happened if this man had

182
00:12:18,140 --> 00:12:22,400
decided yes he would sell everything give it to the poor and come and follow

183
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:27,620
Jesus what would have happened at that moment if he said yes fair enough Lord

184
00:12:27,620 --> 00:12:29,160
Lord, I'll do it.

185
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:32,720
And I can imagine him perhaps getting up and running off,

186
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:35,400
grabbing his checkbook and getting ready to dump it all.

187
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:37,040
He's heading to the ATM.

188
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,460
He's got the card out.

189
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:39,880
He's going to follow through.

190
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,940
And I can almost imagine Jesus saying,

191
00:12:41,980 --> 00:12:42,820
It's okay, stop.

192
00:12:46,710 --> 00:12:47,630
I now have your heart.

193
00:12:50,250 --> 00:12:51,950
Perhaps Jesus would have said,

194
00:12:52,010 --> 00:12:53,930
It's okay, I just want to know that you do it.

195
00:12:54,250 --> 00:12:57,170
Actually, we're going to use your wealth for these things.

196
00:12:57,170 --> 00:13:00,690
You don't know, but I have a suspicion that Jesus would have let him keep it all.

197
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:06,920
And it's easy for us, isn't it, to sit here and say, boy, I'd give it all for Jesus.

198
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:08,700
Really?

199
00:13:11,140 --> 00:13:12,140
Okay, now I'm going to be nasty.

200
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:17,760
If you can't give up one-tenth of your income to Jesus, are you sure you're going to be able to sell it all?

201
00:13:22,490 --> 00:13:27,230
Those who are tithing are a lot closer to that reality, aren't they, than those who don't.

202
00:13:29,460 --> 00:13:32,680
Is Jesus truly Lord of your life?

203
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:37,640
Is Jesus the master of your possessions?

204
00:13:38,140 --> 00:13:38,840
Is he really?

205
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:43,330
Do you love your wealth more than Jesus?

206
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:51,070
Do you really trust him to take care of you when you give him what he's asking of you?

207
00:13:52,980 --> 00:13:57,740
And I've discovered in my life as a Christian that to follow Jesus requires some dying.

208
00:13:57,860 --> 00:13:58,800
We've talked about that.

209
00:13:59,020 --> 00:14:01,860
It requires some dying, some plowing under.

210
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:07,950
But you know, when things are plowed under, they sprout back to new life and they grow.

211
00:14:08,510 --> 00:14:10,670
One thing can make the difference.

212
00:14:11,130 --> 00:14:16,470
Number two, second principle.

213
00:14:16,910 --> 00:14:26,200
about God's blessing is that obedience brings blessings. Obedience brings blessings. When I say

214
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:34,610
that, I realize that I sound like a health and wealth preacher, and I realize that that sounds

215
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:39,690
strange to say because you know that I certainly am not a health and wealth preacher, but I believe

216
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:47,370
the principle still is true. Obedience brings blessings. When you obey God, blessings do come,

217
00:14:47,370 --> 00:14:52,100
And when you disobey God, blessings don't come.

218
00:14:54,810 --> 00:15:00,640
I think the whole Scripture, from A to Z, Alpha and Omega, Genesis to Revelation,

219
00:15:00,860 --> 00:15:03,220
all of it would affirm that reality.

220
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:05,120
When you obey God, there are blessings.

221
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:12,480
When you disobey God, there are non-blessings or curses, bummers, bad things.

222
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:15,360
Follow God, good things. Disobey God, bad things.

223
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:19,900
That seems to be the warp and woof of the Scripture all the way through.

224
00:15:20,380 --> 00:15:30,730
Moses in the wilderness, Israelites, obey God, blessing, disobey God, curses.

225
00:15:32,670 --> 00:15:37,740
Kings, nation follows God, blessings, rebel against God, curses.

226
00:15:38,260 --> 00:15:39,600
It just goes through the prophets.

227
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:41,760
It goes through the whole New Testament as well.

228
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:46,960
Obey God, blessings, ignore God, curses, and anti-blessings.

229
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:53,040
Blessing and judgment came as a result of following God.

230
00:15:53,380 --> 00:15:54,700
Matthew 6.33,

231
00:15:55,910 --> 00:15:57,810
Your heavenly Father already knows your needs.

232
00:15:59,190 --> 00:16:01,590
And He will give you all you need from day to day

233
00:16:01,590 --> 00:16:02,990
if you live for Him

234
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:05,890
and make the kingdom of God your primary concern.

235
00:16:06,890 --> 00:16:09,010
We know that verse traditionally like this,

236
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:13,100
but seek first His kingdom and His righteousness

237
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:17,390
and all these things shall be added unto you.

238
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:23,260
You know it. You've heard it.

239
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,680
But do you believe it?

240
00:16:27,670 --> 00:16:31,930
Do we really believe that God will provide for us and take care of us

241
00:16:31,930 --> 00:16:35,710
when we stretch and give him what he's asking of us?

242
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:40,300
Do you believe it enough to change your lifestyle

243
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:43,200
so you can be obedient and give the Lord the tithe?

244
00:16:44,150 --> 00:16:45,550
And I know this is tough.

245
00:16:46,980 --> 00:16:49,220
And I know that you are just squirming

246
00:16:49,220 --> 00:16:55,480
and wish I'd get out of the pulpit and stop this horrendous onslaught.

247
00:16:55,540 --> 00:16:57,280
Oh, please, it's almost over, isn't it?

248
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:57,960
No, not yet.

249
00:16:58,460 --> 00:16:59,580
I'm only on page six.

250
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:06,340
Our money is a sacred area, and that's why Jesus talked about it so much.

251
00:17:07,230 --> 00:17:09,170
Because it's so close to us.

252
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:16,010
And I really believe that what we believe is reflected in how we use our money.

253
00:17:16,670 --> 00:17:19,090
I really have come to see that in my own life.

254
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:22,580
I believe it's true in your lives as well.

255
00:17:23,420 --> 00:17:25,440
Let's talk about something right here.

256
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:30,250
Last year at our annual meeting, we voted as a church body

257
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:33,630
to approve a large increase in our budget.

258
00:17:34,210 --> 00:17:40,330
And we jumped from a number in the low fives to $600,000 in one bump.

259
00:17:40,670 --> 00:17:42,770
That was a 20% increase.

260
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,580
And the council said, God can do this through us.

261
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,060
We're going to buy off.

262
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:52,080
And unanimously, the council said, we're doing this.

263
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:55,580
We presented that to you at the meeting last year in January,

264
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:59,320
and we voted to take on that kind of budget.

265
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:01,340
Now, let's be honest.

266
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:05,660
At first glance, $600,000 budget seems really large.

267
00:18:06,540 --> 00:18:07,320
It really does.

268
00:18:08,340 --> 00:18:11,000
And those numbers just seem astronomical to some of us.

269
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:11,980
But you know what?

270
00:18:12,220 --> 00:18:13,060
They're really not.

271
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:14,180
Let me tell you why not.

272
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:16,980
Because let me get really straight with you.

273
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:22,560
If everybody in this church who actually call themselves members of this ministry

274
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:27,360
and followers of Jesus Christ, devoted to him as leader and Lord of your life,

275
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:32,640
if we took God seriously and all of us tithed whatever God has blessed us with,

276
00:18:33,020 --> 00:18:36,300
we would have a budget over a million dollars.

277
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:39,200
Over a million dollars.

278
00:18:40,820 --> 00:18:46,520
And I scratch my head and think all the things that God could do with a budget over a million dollars.

279
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:51,800
The kinds of staff we could hire to do amazing things in this church

280
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:54,200
and in this community with a million dollars.

281
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:56,820
And we're a little over half of that.

282
00:18:56,820 --> 00:19:07,200
and as we're running behind, I just get sad

283
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:13,780
because I think it's tragic because when God speaks to the council

284
00:19:13,780 --> 00:19:17,780
and the council wrestles with God together and what we think

285
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:22,000
God wants us to stretch and to do and then for us to be disobedient

286
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:25,800
and to say, well, I trust you sort of but not really and to

287
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:29,900
hold back and we struggle with our budget and I have to write nasty letters and I hate

288
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:34,500
doing that type of stuff. I would rather come up here every year

289
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:36,800
and say, you're giving too much.

290
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:38,900
It's okay.

291
00:19:39,340 --> 00:19:40,040
Calm down.

292
00:19:40,910 --> 00:19:41,930
We've got a million two.

293
00:19:42,010 --> 00:19:43,070
We don't even need that.

294
00:19:43,690 --> 00:19:44,950
A million one is all we need.

295
00:19:46,210 --> 00:19:46,710
So go ahead.

296
00:19:46,850 --> 00:19:47,690
You take that home.

297
00:19:48,430 --> 00:19:50,650
Boy, I'd love to say that to you.

298
00:19:51,210 --> 00:19:52,070
I really would.

299
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:57,130
So I sit here and I say, Lord, you can do 600.

300
00:19:57,310 --> 00:19:58,170
You can do a lot more.

301
00:19:58,370 --> 00:19:59,570
I've got a lot bigger dreams.

302
00:19:59,650 --> 00:20:01,090
The council's got a lot bigger dreams.

303
00:20:01,290 --> 00:20:03,230
We're just getting started here in Fullerton.

304
00:20:05,350 --> 00:20:07,110
21st century has just begun.

305
00:20:08,330 --> 00:20:13,230
And there's lost people all around that need to be reached and discipled and trained and sent back out.

306
00:20:13,530 --> 00:20:16,530
I want to host a whole flock of ministries and missionaries.

307
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:18,500
Not just a few.

308
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:21,740
I want to pack this place out three times.

309
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:26,840
I've shared with you before, our ministry here can handle 1,200 people in this building.

310
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:29,780
Two or three services, a few over there.

311
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:32,280
We've got to go there.

312
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:33,760
We've got to go there.

313
00:20:34,940 --> 00:20:36,640
And beyond that, I want to plant churches.

314
00:20:38,050 --> 00:20:42,330
I have such big dreams for this church as a leading church in our denomination.

315
00:20:42,830 --> 00:20:46,450
We are being looked at by everybody else as to what God is doing here.

316
00:20:46,450 --> 00:20:51,010
Do you realize as we taught seminars, as we led seminars in this training in Vegas,

317
00:20:51,430 --> 00:20:53,590
that pastors and leaders came up to us and said,

318
00:20:53,890 --> 00:20:54,750
tell us what you're doing.

319
00:20:55,030 --> 00:20:57,610
Teach us, pastor, youth pastors, everybody.

320
00:20:57,850 --> 00:20:58,890
What's happening there?

321
00:20:59,110 --> 00:20:59,790
What are we doing?

322
00:21:00,010 --> 00:21:03,430
And I'm excited to be a leader, to train, and to lead as a denomination.

323
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:05,910
And then I come back and go, man, we're not even making our budget.

324
00:21:05,910 --> 00:21:07,850
and I get frustrated by that.

325
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:14,660
$600,000 should be a spit in the bucket for us

326
00:21:14,660 --> 00:21:17,990
and I want to go bigger

327
00:21:17,990 --> 00:21:21,540
and I'm just going to challenge you

328
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:23,100
to get serious with God

329
00:21:23,100 --> 00:21:26,470
and to say, Lord, what are we going to do?

330
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:29,580
And friends, we got a big old debt hanging over

331
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:31,460
that we're going to pay down in the next three years

332
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:34,710
so we can be free and clear of that kind of thing

333
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:37,100
so we can really go after ministry

334
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:38,200
in some powerful ways.

335
00:21:39,020 --> 00:21:40,360
And it's going to be challenging three years

336
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:41,560
but I think we're going to learn

337
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,840
what it means to trust Jesus together

338
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:45,000
and hold each other accountable.

339
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:47,020
It's going to be fun and exciting

340
00:21:47,020 --> 00:21:50,240
and I'm looking forward to the next three years

341
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,340
as we dive into that.

342
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:53,380
But I want us to be faithful

343
00:21:53,380 --> 00:21:57,000
and to be stewards of what God has given us.

344
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,480
We are the managers.

345
00:21:58,800 --> 00:21:59,920
God is the blesser.

346
00:22:00,460 --> 00:22:01,460
Do we trust him?

347
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:02,580
Are we going to be obedient?

348
00:22:03,020 --> 00:22:04,580
Or do we just want to go to Blockbuster

349
00:22:04,580 --> 00:22:05,900
and hold on to the five bucks?

350
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:08,300
It's really, what are the 50 bucks?

351
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:09,760
What are the 500 bucks?

352
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:11,380
Or whatever case you're in,

353
00:22:11,380 --> 00:22:13,940
Are we going to hold back, or are we going to trust the Lord?

354
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:19,300
Seek first God's kingdom, and the rest will be added unto you.

355
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:20,540
Do you believe that?

356
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:23,820
We either believe it or not.

357
00:22:24,630 --> 00:22:26,010
We either believe it or we don't.

358
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:31,060
And as I shared before, I'm living proof of that reality.

359
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:36,100
As much as I yell and scream at you, I've sat where you are, I've held on to my checkbook,

360
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:37,920
and I've said, but Lord, you don't understand.

361
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:39,780
I've given everything to this church.

362
00:22:39,860 --> 00:22:42,460
I stay up until 2 a.m. all the time with these kids.

363
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,600
I don't have enough money.

364
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,200
I can barely pay the cable bill.

365
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:47,130
Do I need a cable bill?

366
00:22:47,950 --> 00:22:48,530
Good question.

367
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:50,480
I've sat where you are.

368
00:22:50,820 --> 00:22:51,840
I've looked at the bills.

369
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,640
I've looked at things in my own life.

370
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:59,360
And when Robin and I got serious about saying, Lord, you first and everything else second,

371
00:22:59,860 --> 00:23:02,660
then blessing came into our life.

372
00:23:03,460 --> 00:23:06,620
Not just material, but blessing overall.

373
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:12,920
But it started when we really stopped holding back from God and began to trust Him.

374
00:23:14,180 --> 00:23:17,720
And we have discovered in our own life, when you trust Him with your finances and He meets you there,

375
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,920
it's easier to trust Him in other areas of your life as well.

376
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:25,520
But the financial seems to be the most potent because it's the closest to us

377
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:28,540
and it's right there in front of us all the time.

378
00:23:30,260 --> 00:23:33,190
So I know where you are.

379
00:23:33,530 --> 00:23:34,190
I'm struggling.

380
00:23:34,310 --> 00:23:36,470
I know the pressure you're feeling right now.

381
00:23:37,210 --> 00:23:37,890
I've been there.

382
00:23:38,330 --> 00:23:39,630
Sometimes I'm still there.

383
00:23:41,170 --> 00:23:44,130
But I'm challenging you and I'm challenging me to be obedient to Jesus

384
00:23:44,130 --> 00:23:48,290
and to give him his due and allow him to grow and minister through the church

385
00:23:48,290 --> 00:23:52,720
and bless you back, tenfold will you be obedient.

386
00:23:55,290 --> 00:23:57,290
Obedience brings blessings, Luke chapter 6.

387
00:23:57,370 --> 00:23:58,950
If you forgive others, you'll be forgiven.

388
00:23:58,950 --> 00:24:01,380
If you give, you will receive.

389
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:05,720
Your gift returns to you full measure, pressed down, shaken together

390
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:07,800
to make room for more and running over.

391
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:11,360
Whatever measure you use in giving, large or small,

392
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:14,340
it will be used to measure what is given back to you.

393
00:24:15,870 --> 00:24:18,650
Proverbs chapter 3, honor the Lord with your wealth

394
00:24:18,650 --> 00:24:21,770
and with the best part of everything your land produces.

395
00:24:23,690 --> 00:24:25,150
Then he's going to fill your barns with grain,

396
00:24:25,250 --> 00:24:27,250
your vats with overflow, with the finest wine.

397
00:24:30,170 --> 00:24:33,090
Proverbs chapter 11, the generous prosper and are satisfied.

398
00:24:33,090 --> 00:24:34,930
The generous prosper.

399
00:24:37,450 --> 00:24:41,520
Those who refresh others become refreshed.

400
00:24:43,340 --> 00:24:44,560
To get, you've got to give.

401
00:24:47,010 --> 00:24:49,610
Blessed are those who are generous, says Proverbs 22,

402
00:24:50,010 --> 00:24:52,170
because they feed the poor, in verse 9.

403
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,620
Blessed are those who are generous.

404
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:59,080
You will receive blessing and happiness and peace when you are generous.

405
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:03,290
And here's the doozy.

406
00:25:04,730 --> 00:25:05,810
Malachi chapter 3.

407
00:25:06,270 --> 00:25:07,910
Should people cheat God?

408
00:25:09,380 --> 00:25:10,960
And God says, yet you have cheated me.

409
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:13,780
But you ask, what do you mean?

410
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:14,820
When do we ever cheat you?

411
00:25:16,210 --> 00:25:18,990
You have cheated me of the tithes and offerings due to me.

412
00:25:19,250 --> 00:25:22,090
You are under a curse for the whole nation has been cheating me.

413
00:25:22,650 --> 00:25:24,870
Bring all your tithes into the storehouse

414
00:25:24,870 --> 00:25:27,050
so there will be enough food in my temple.

415
00:25:27,050 --> 00:25:31,610
If you do, says the Lord Almighty, I will open the windows of heaven for you.

416
00:25:32,420 --> 00:25:35,740
I will pour out a blessing so great you won't have enough room to take it in.

417
00:25:36,180 --> 00:25:36,820
Try it.

418
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,600
Let me prove it to you.

419
00:25:40,150 --> 00:25:44,070
As I've said before, that's the only verse in the Bible I know where God says, test me in this.

420
00:25:47,540 --> 00:25:50,240
God cursed the whole nation over this issue.

421
00:25:51,940 --> 00:25:52,740
Curses or blessings.

422
00:25:53,060 --> 00:25:54,140
Curses or blessings.

423
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:56,900
I personally want to live under blessing.

424
00:25:57,980 --> 00:26:00,600
That's the selfish self-preservationist part of me.

425
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:01,580
I want to live under blessing.

426
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:02,620
Blessings are curses.

427
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:03,380
I'll take blessings.

428
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:04,240
Thank you very much.

429
00:26:04,460 --> 00:26:05,400
What do I need to do?

430
00:26:06,690 --> 00:26:07,450
Trust the Lord.

431
00:26:08,390 --> 00:26:08,890
Got it.

432
00:26:09,410 --> 00:26:09,770
Okay.

433
00:26:10,350 --> 00:26:10,670
Good.

434
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:14,840
Obedience brings blessings.

435
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:18,320
Is the Bible true or not?

436
00:26:19,030 --> 00:26:20,210
Do we really want to follow Jesus?

437
00:26:22,820 --> 00:26:23,880
I just want to say it again.

438
00:26:23,880 --> 00:26:29,300
If you don't put the Lord first in your finances, you're not going to receive all that God has for you.

439
00:26:31,180 --> 00:26:31,580
Simple.

440
00:26:33,410 --> 00:26:34,950
And one thing can make a difference.

441
00:26:37,230 --> 00:26:38,310
Obedience brings blessing.

442
00:26:39,340 --> 00:26:44,140
And finally this, team God, number three.

443
00:26:45,650 --> 00:26:46,590
Whose team are you on?

444
00:26:48,370 --> 00:26:49,830
I want to be on God's team.

445
00:26:50,430 --> 00:26:51,950
I want our church to be on God's team.

446
00:26:54,740 --> 00:26:58,620
And Paul, in a great letter about joy and contentment,

447
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:01,280
challenges us and wants to know what team we're on.

448
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:02,900
Philippians 4.19,

449
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:06,520
At the same God who takes care of me, says Paul while writing from prison,

450
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:09,660
will supply all your needs from his glorious riches,

451
00:27:09,820 --> 00:27:12,720
which have been given to us in Christ Jesus.

452
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:14,220
How many needs?

453
00:27:15,110 --> 00:27:15,950
All your needs.

454
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:23,740
It doesn't say all of our wants, all of our needs.

455
00:27:25,820 --> 00:27:29,100
We do confuse needs and wants in our culture, don't we?

456
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:31,820
I need to have that.

457
00:27:33,220 --> 00:27:33,760
Maybe not.

458
00:27:35,610 --> 00:27:36,430
I want that.

459
00:27:36,490 --> 00:27:37,030
That's fair.

460
00:27:38,230 --> 00:27:40,810
But God will take care of your needs, it says.

461
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:48,100
So do you want to be on God's team and partner with him and trust him, allow him to bless you?

462
00:27:49,940 --> 00:27:52,260
On God's team, all the players do their part.

463
00:27:52,260 --> 00:27:56,180
watching the Angels this year.

464
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:57,880
Here's a team

465
00:27:57,880 --> 00:28:00,980
where I have not perceived

466
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:02,800
that any one particular player

467
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:04,680
is a superstar more than the others.

468
00:28:05,930 --> 00:28:07,270
I mean, there's some really good players,

469
00:28:07,650 --> 00:28:10,770
but the egos seem to be in check on that team.

470
00:28:11,070 --> 00:28:13,890
There seems to be a real team spirit

471
00:28:13,890 --> 00:28:15,970
where that monkey rally thing comes out

472
00:28:15,970 --> 00:28:17,550
and boom, those guys work together.

473
00:28:18,130 --> 00:28:19,410
And they encourage each other.

474
00:28:19,410 --> 00:28:20,610
And they're going to the top

475
00:28:20,610 --> 00:28:22,430
because they've been a team together.

476
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:26,620
It's not one superstar taking the ball

477
00:28:26,620 --> 00:28:29,560
and carrying it through and the rest riding on their coattails.

478
00:28:30,370 --> 00:28:33,840
They're all involved, and they're all into it,

479
00:28:35,130 --> 00:28:39,170
encouraging the other, knocking those arms and the fist thing and all that stuff.

480
00:28:39,770 --> 00:28:44,110
They love each other, and it seems to be an image of the body of Christ in some ways,

481
00:28:44,350 --> 00:28:47,710
working together to go to where God is calling us to go.

482
00:28:47,890 --> 00:28:49,470
But we all have to do our part.

483
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:53,860
And if some of us are riding on the coattails of others,

484
00:28:54,760 --> 00:28:57,260
we're missing being a part of the team,

485
00:28:57,260 --> 00:29:02,230
and we miss the blessing that God can pour on the individual life

486
00:29:02,230 --> 00:29:06,430
and you hold back the team from going all the way.

487
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:12,900
Okay, team players, are we going to be team players?

488
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,500
And I'm going to ask you this in conclusion.

489
00:29:16,500 --> 00:29:20,800
Will you go home this week and think and pray about your stewardship

490
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:23,200
both this year and the next?

491
00:29:24,850 --> 00:29:29,090
Will you get really serious before God and take your checkbook

492
00:29:29,090 --> 00:29:32,030
and if need be your spouse, if that's appropriate,

493
00:29:32,030 --> 00:29:35,030
and just kneel before the bed and lay it there and say,

494
00:29:35,030 --> 00:29:37,210
Lord God, we're going to put you first.

495
00:29:37,330 --> 00:29:40,780
Help us to do that and to trust you with that.

496
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:46,200
In a couple weeks, we're going to be pledging our commitments for next year.

497
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:49,500
It's an important part of our budgeting process.

498
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:51,680
I want us to make our budget.

499
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:53,380
I want us to not just make it.

500
00:29:53,840 --> 00:29:57,460
I want us to blow through it so we have reserves before we even start next year.

501
00:29:59,220 --> 00:30:04,220
I hate going into the next year writing off a big chunk of money on the books

502
00:30:04,220 --> 00:30:07,890
and sliding to the next year and evening it all out,

503
00:30:07,930 --> 00:30:08,610
but we didn't make it.

504
00:30:08,630 --> 00:30:09,330
I hate that.

505
00:30:11,460 --> 00:30:13,520
And God's people, we shouldn't be living like that.

506
00:30:14,870 --> 00:30:16,270
We really shouldn't be like that.

507
00:30:17,950 --> 00:30:19,290
We could have a million dollars.

508
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:28,250
Six is nothing if we just get serious with God.

509
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:33,020
And I just can't wait to see what God's going to do through you

510
00:30:33,020 --> 00:30:37,340
as we get prayerfully down our knees and go after this.

511
00:30:37,900 --> 00:30:40,760
I am so looking forward to seeing your pledge cards coming in

512
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:42,080
and what God's going to do in this church

513
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:45,160
and how we're going to raise up new people and train new people

514
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:51,300
and grab on a new staff and just send and just keep being a leader in this region

515
00:30:51,300 --> 00:30:54,150
and being all that God's calling us to be.

516
00:30:54,210 --> 00:30:55,290
I can't wait to see that.

517
00:30:55,970 --> 00:30:58,010
And so I'm going to pray a blessing on you

518
00:30:58,010 --> 00:31:03,140
as you ask God to bless you as you bless him by putting him first.

519
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:03,960
Let's pray.

520
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:12,060
Father, I love this congregation and I know the struggle in putting you first in our finances.

521
00:31:12,260 --> 00:31:13,300
Father, I've been there.

522
00:31:13,300 --> 00:31:21,500
Sometimes I'm still there because, boy, it really puts this belief thing to the test.

523
00:31:23,420 --> 00:31:27,020
But, Lord, I pray that we as a church body would be faithful,

524
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:32,000
that your spirit would right now be moving and touching us and convicting us

525
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:36,320
and encouraging us, showing us how we can trust you.

526
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:39,500
And, Lord, I pray you're going to meet their needs and bless them.

527
00:31:39,740 --> 00:31:42,900
And through our obedience that we're going to see amazing things happen

528
00:31:42,900 --> 00:31:45,500
and that we'll be even more encouraged to trust you more

529
00:31:45,500 --> 00:31:48,670
in all kinds of areas of ministry

530
00:31:48,670 --> 00:31:53,340
and that we'll really be the faithful beacon

531
00:31:53,340 --> 00:31:54,540
of hope and love

532
00:31:54,540 --> 00:31:57,460
that I believe, Lord, you're calling us to be.

533
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:03,340
So, Lord, we look forward to seeing that happen.

534
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:06,860
So, Lord, take the truth of these scriptures

535
00:32:06,860 --> 00:32:07,940
and make them real.

536
00:32:08,870 --> 00:32:11,110
To me and to each one in this room,

537
00:32:11,210 --> 00:32:12,630
make these scriptures real

538
00:32:12,630 --> 00:32:16,050
and I pray we'd be faithful

539
00:32:16,050 --> 00:32:18,100
and trust you.

540
00:32:20,080 --> 00:32:21,740
Help us step out of our zone of comfort

541
00:32:21,740 --> 00:32:23,420
and may you meet us right there

542
00:32:23,420 --> 00:32:25,210
and hold us up.

543
00:32:27,800 --> 00:32:31,640
So, Father, pour out your blessing, I pray, as we become obedient to you.

544
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:43,270
As we're just meditating on those thoughts, I just want to say to those this morning as our heads are bowed,

545
00:32:43,310 --> 00:32:48,610
that if you, even though you've sat through a sermon and a message about giving,

546
00:32:48,610 --> 00:32:54,090
you're realizing, though, that this Lord Jesus that we're asking, that we give our whole lives to,

547
00:32:54,130 --> 00:32:55,530
and you realize you haven't done that yet.

548
00:32:56,810 --> 00:32:57,770
You've been holding back.

549
00:32:58,980 --> 00:33:00,060
You know he's there.

550
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:03,640
You realize that he's true.

551
00:33:05,220 --> 00:33:10,240
Perhaps you need to just, in the quietness of your heart right now,

552
00:33:10,340 --> 00:33:11,300
just pray this prayer.

553
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:13,620
I would encourage you to pray along with me.

554
00:33:14,590 --> 00:33:20,060
Dear God, I realize that you are the director of heaven

555
00:33:20,060 --> 00:33:22,780
and the leader and the forgiver of my life.

556
00:33:24,230 --> 00:33:27,650
And I want to start fresh and new and live a life that's under blessing

557
00:33:27,650 --> 00:33:32,010
instead of where I've been, which I can clearly see now is under curses.

558
00:33:32,490 --> 00:33:39,650
I want to be free of all of that and turn and be all about you and your team.

559
00:33:39,690 --> 00:33:43,730
and I want new life that starts now

560
00:33:43,730 --> 00:33:44,710
and ends in forever

561
00:33:44,710 --> 00:33:46,270
that never ends

562
00:33:46,270 --> 00:33:48,360
so I'm yours

563
00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:51,500
and I pray this in Jesus name

564
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:58,560
as we're standing to sing our final song

